Failing to reach a deal on how to address the ongoing health & economic crises caused by #COVID19 is unacceptable - a failure of duty to the American people.

That’s why I joined @RepGolden & 16 other Rs & Ds in urging @SpeakerPelosi @GOPLeader to immediately resume negotiations. https://t.co/J5RHiEdoSQ

Last month, I introduced the RESTART Act w/ @MikeKellyPA to help Maine's hardest-hit small businesses as they continue to struggle.

RESTART builds on & improves the PPP with flexible, long-term, partially forgivable loans that covers:
- Payroll
- Rent
- PPE
- Utilities (& more)

We are excited to be participating in a forum with the @HouseSmallBiz ! We are joined by our clients from Farmington Underground who are speaking about their experience during COVID and as an SBDC client. Thank you @RepGolden  for the opportunity. 
 https://t.co/U0El7uZPlp https://t.co/UpNYILpbGo

full_text:
Today, I'm leading the @HouseSmallBiz Subcommittee I chair to hear from small business owners who've used SBDCs to keep their business running, and SBDC directors from across the country. 2/ #mepolitics

We're starting in a few minutes. Follow along here: https://t.co/0QSWeUMq2f

The first presumptive positive test for coronavirus has been reported in Maine.

It’s up to each of us to protect the most vulnerable Mainers. Start with these steps:
- Wash your hands often
- Cover your coughs
- Stay home if you’re sick
- Clean & disinfect high-contact surfaces

retweeted_text:
When workers have the power to stand together and form a union, they have:
- Bigger paychecks 
- Better benefits
- Safer working conditions
Today, @RepGolden will help pass the #PROAct to help create an economy where everyone can succeed. #1u

full_text:
I’m not afraid to fight for unions and workers’ rights. When House leaders wouldn’t bring up the #PROAct for a vote, I led a group of 75 Members of Congress to bring the bill up for a vote. 

That vote takes place tonight and I'm confident we'll pass this bill through the House.

full_text:
For decades, the power of working people to organize & stand up for their rights has been stripped away. The results have been predictable. In the last 40 yrs:
- the top 1% of earned 200% more
- income for working folks barely budged.

That's why we need #PROActNow

My letter to CMP today: https://t.co/e25woRZUWh

That's why we passed a bipartisan ban on drilling for oil and gas off the coast of Maine though the House last month. Find out more here: https://t.co/Li9eTyLjc1

This is a basic step for good policy-making, but NOAA blew by it. Sound science and good data shouldn’t be too much to expect. 3/

The non-partisan CBO estimates that the Rx drug provisions in today’s bill will save our country around $4 billion over 10 years.

That's not much compared to the $333 billion paid by gov, consumers, & insurers on prescription drugs in 2017 alone.

We *HAVE* to do more. 3/

This common-sense bill:
1️⃣ Reinstates #NetNeutrality for a free and open internet
2️⃣ Takes power back for consumers
3️⃣ Helps expand rural broadband and create jobs through programs like the Connect America Fund

Today, we took action to restore our democracy & make government work #ForthePeople. The bill we passed today:

Via @NewsCenterMaine https://t.co/p50RurKbLt

How do corporations get away with this? 

When they develop a new drug, the gov’t gives Rx companies a years-long monopoly. They can skyrocket prices with no competition. It’s a system intended to promote R&D, but many pharma companies abuse it on the backs of Maine people.

We rode along with Androscoggin Home Healthcare & Hospice to learn how we can help them provide quality, affordable care to Maine seniors & others. https://t.co/LiRKzhMOKN

Heidi Gerding’s small biz took a $100,000+ hit from the gov't shutdown. Losses that big would cripple some family businesses in Maine.

In @HouseSmallBiz today, we focused on helping small biz who haven’t recovered from the shutdown. 

Watch more here: https://t.co/CYzeAAW2aX

Proud to be working with @RepGolden @RepDanCrenshaw to bring some sense to this town. https://t.co/7yxKHpem4h

I'm introducing the bipartisan Solidarity in Salary Act today with @RepDanCrenshaw and @RepMaxRose to withhold pay from Congress, @POTUS,  & @vp during a shutdown. https://t.co/Cjb5xcIAPy

full_text:
We opened our offices in Lewiston and Caribou this week! 
We're here to listen to and work for Maine people. If you need assistance with federal programs like Medicare, Social Security, and the VA, we're here to help.

Lewiston: 179 Lisbon St. 

Caribou: 7 Hatch Drive, Suite 230 https://t.co/1kXSEtm7TM

Just finished my first day as a Congressman. I am honored and proud to represent Maine's second district. 

Today, we took a critical step to end the partial government shutdown. But that's just the beginning. We're ready to listen, get to work, and put people first. https://t.co/AG4OEJdC6B
